Brandon Afoa was operating a tug to push aircraft at Seattle-Tacoma International Airport when the brakes and steering failed and he crashed into a luggage lift in December 2007 . 
  The accident left him paralyzed from the waist down and he was unable to use his legs or right arm . 
  He sued the Port of Seattle - which owns and operates the airport - saying the company failed to maintain a safe workplace . 
  On Tuesday he was awarded $40 million in compensation . 
 